✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Fun and unique problem! Nice idea and it is enjoyable to figure out the solution.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: An original puzzle that is perfect for the Clash of Code environment. Good job!

I like it and gave it an upvote.

Two minor suggestions:

Suggest to change this:
Package name is lowercase may contain numbers, multiple underscores and dashes. 
to
Package name is lowercase; it may contain numbers, multiple underscores and dashes. 

Suggest to change this:
Given are the number of packages. Followed by a list of installed versions and a list of available versions. 
to
Given are the number of packages, followed by a list of installed versions and a list of available versions.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Very clear description, simple yet useful puzzle to solve. Good job !

Goal section
* You may remove the example as it just duplicates the one shown below.

Constraint section
* N is 100 in the last validator, and it violates the constraint 1<N<100. Please fix either the constraint or the case.
* Please format N, x, y, z as [[variables]].
* Please change "my" to "may".

Thanks.
